'''Lewis Galoob Toys''' was a toy company that was bought by [[Hasbro Inc.|Hasbro]]. Galoob released several waves of ''[[Star Wars]]'' playsets and figures during its run, including the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire Micro Machines|''Shadows of the Empire'' Micro Machines]] set in [[1996]] and the ''[[Micro Machines Epic Collections]]'' sets.

==History==
Galoob participated to the ''[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]'' project and produced figures of the characters (both [[Original trilogy|original]] and [[Star Wars Legends|new]]) and six vehicles of the story. In the spring of [[1996]] (according to projections) 100,000 units were released under the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire Micro Machines|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' Micro Machines]] brand.<ref>''[[The Secrets of Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]''</ref>

In [[1997]], Galoob discontinued all of its other [[Gender|male]] action toy lines to focus exclusively on its ''Star Wars'' toys, which it called its "most important asset".<ref>''Kidscreen'', [https://kidscreen.com/1997/12/01/20063-19971201 Galoob sticks with Star Wars] by Kidscreen Staff. [[December 1]], [[1997]].</ref> On [[September 29]], [[1998]],<ref name="YBY" /> [[Hasbro Inc.]] acquired Galoob for $220 million.<ref name="SFChronicle">{{WebCite|url=https://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Hasbro-Adds-Galoob-to-Its-Toy-Chest-2988518.php|text=Hasbro Adds Galoob to Its Toy Chest|work=the ''San Francisco Chronicle''|date=1998-09-29|archiveurl=https://archive.is/wCxg}}</ref>

